o use a Wavecrasher in the main hand and a Blade of the Black Dragon Eye (14/24 with a poison based 30DD + 200 DoT).  The Slow + DoT of the Wavecrasher along with the Warrior Epic style ratio and proc on the BotBDE SHOULD (you would think) have always kept me at the top of the hate list.<br>
<br>
Maybe a year ago, but not now.  2h slashing has been given a dramatic boost at some point in the last year and now the damage bonus is completely insane.  Pallies with Windblades were regularly taking agro from me without taunt or spell casting.  Even with Boon of the Garou and a 255 dexterity I would still need to use the taunt key frequently to maintain agro.<br>
<br>
I recently (last night) bought a Stone Axe of Dismay (44/44) and even with a skill of only 80-110 I was regularly taking agro from the MT in the group that was using Wavecrasher and a 10/20 hammer with Snare.  I mean we all know what an agro snare can be right ?  Yet I would still get the mob on me WITHOUT taunt if I simply got a double attack for 100+ each hit.<br>
<br>
I grew up on the premise that &quot;1hs &gt; ALL where damage per second is concerned&quot;.  Now with Windblade giving me a 37 damage bonus, not even a Shortblade of Lightning and Fleshgrinder could give me better DPS and better agro.<br>
<br>
I mean let's put it this way, a RANGER I was talking to said he had been parsing his DPS with 2 one-handers vs. his Windblade and found he was doing a consistant 30% more DPM with Windblade.  Let's face it - rangers have access to better ratio's on the 1 handers than we do so this pretty much seals the deal.<br>
<br>
I'm gonna work up my 2h slashing to max and acquire a Windblade to test 1h vs. 2h but I already know what the results will be - Windblade &gt; all pre-ST 1 handers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
